  "prompt": "What does \"designation\" mean on a form?",
  "response": "The term \"designation\" on a form typically refers to a title, position, or label that identifies a person\u2019s role, function, or classification in a certain context. For example, on a job application, \"designation\" might refer to the applicant's job title (like \"Software Engineer\" or \"Project Manager\"). In other contexts, it could refer to the status or category of a person (like \"Doctor,\" \"Student,\" or \"Manager\"). Essentially, it helps to clarify the individual's identity or role related to the form's purpose.",
